---
description: Docstrings (PEP 257)
globs:
  - "**/*.py"  # Apply to all Python files
  - "**/*.pyi" # Apply to Python stub files
alwaysApply: true
---

Write clear, concise, and informative docstrings for all public modules, classes, functions, and methods, adhering to PEP 257 conventions (e.g., Google style or NumPy style). Explain the purpose, arguments ($Args:$), return values ($Returns:$), and any exceptions raised ($Raises:$).

